RunInfo:
  'Proton-proton interactions at 8 TeV centre-of-mass energy.
   $Z$ bosons are fully reconstructed from the $\mu^- \mu^+$ decay channel.
   NOTE: this means that Z bosons should be undecayed in the event generator,
   e.g. 23:mayDecay=no in Pythia, while other unstable particles are decayed as normal.'
Beams: [p+, p+]
Energies: [[4000,4000]]
Luminosity_fb: 2.0
Description:
  'The LHCb Collaboration presents measurements of the longitudinal, transverse, and radial
   distributions of charged hadrons in $Z$-jets using proton-proton data collected at a 
   center-of-mass energy of $\sqrt{s} = 8$TeV. $Z$ bosons are fully reconstructed from the
   $\mu^- \mu^+$ decay channel. Jets with transverse momentum $p_\mathrm{T,jet} > 20$ GeV are
   reconstructed within the rapidity range $2.5 < y_\mathrm{jet} < 4.0$ using the anti-$k_\mathrm{T}$
   algorithm with resolution paparmeter $R = 0.5$.'
ValidationInfo:
  'Validation used Pythia 8.244 with Rivet 3.1.11. The 4C tune was used (Tune:pp=5). Pythia curves
   in the LHCb publication use the LHCb Tune, which is based on 4C. All QCD channels
   were used (HardQCD:all=on) to generate events with a Z-boson at parton level (HadronLevel:all=off),
   which was then hadronized. For simplicity, a single pTHat bin with PhaseSpace:pTHatMin=10 was used.'
